definitions.definition: Alternative form of encumbrance ( “ that which encumbers ” ) .
An interest , right , burden , or liability attached to a title of land , such as a lien or mortgage .
One who is dependent on another.

main_definition: Alternative form of encumbrance ( “ that which encumbers ” ) .
